Package FMS.entities

Class ScheduledFlight

  • Object
    • FMS.entities.Flight
      • FMS.entities.ScheduledFlight
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<Flight>
    public class ScheduledFlight
extends Flight
    A scheduled flight in the flight management system (FMS). The amount of bonus miles awarded for a scheduled flight is the distance rounded down to full thousands of miles, e.g. 5432 is rounded down to 5000.
    Author:
    TeM

      • ScheduledFlight

        public ScheduledFlight​(String flightID,
                       String origin,
                       String destination,
                       DateTime departure,
                       DateTime arrival,
                       int distance)
        Creates a scheduled flight with an id, an origin, a destination and both departure and arrival as well as distance.
        Calls the super constructor. Invalid distance argument is ignored.
        Parameters:
        flightID - the id of this flight
        origin - the origin of this flight
        destination - the destination of this flight
        departure - the scheduled departure date and time of this flight
        arrival - the scheduled arrival date and time of this flight
        distance - the distance of this flight
        See Also:
        Flight(String, String, String, DateTime, DateTime)
